## Description
This refactors the exception handling for JSON API and GraphQL into exception handler implementations that are configured on `JsonApiSettings` and `GraphQLSettings` respectively.

The `isVerbose` method has been removed from the `PermissionExecutor` interface and is now the `isVerboseErrors` property on `ElideSettings`. The `VerbosePermissionExecutor` has as a consequence been removed. A `PermissionExecutor` with the `RequestScope` can still access the verbose setting from the `RequestScope` by getting `ElideSettings` and its `isVerboseErrors` property. It was previously awkward to determine the `isVerbose` setting without an instance of a `PermissionExecutor`.

`ElideResponse` was refactored to have a type parameter as a body. `ElideErrorResponse` then extends off `ElideResponse` and has `ElideErrors` as a body.

The `ErrorMapper` which mapped an exception to a `CustomErrorException` has been replaced by an `ExceptionMapper` that maps an exception to an `ElideErrorResponse` which contains `ElideErrors` as a body. The respective `DefaultJsonApiExceptionHandler` and `DefaultGraphQLExceptionHandler` will map the `ElideErrors` body to the respective `JsonApiErrors` and `GraphQLErrors`.

For Spring Boot customizing the exception mapping just requires exposing an `ExceptionMapper` bean.

```java
@Component
public class InvalidEntityBodyExceptionMapper implements ExceptionMapper<InvalidEntityBodyException, ElideErrors> {
    public ElideErrorResponse<ElideErrors> toErrorResponse(InvalidEntityBodyException exception, ErrorContext errorContext) {
        return ElideErrorResponse.badRequest()
            .errors(errors -> errors.error(error -> error.message("Invalid entity body")));
    }
}
```

For Standalone the `ElideStandaloneSettings getExceptionMappers` function needs to be overridden.

```java
public abstract class Settings implements ElideStandaloneSettings {
    @Override
    public ExceptionMappers getExceptionMappers() {
        return BasicExceptionMappers.builder().register(new InvalidEntityBodyExceptionMapper()).build();
    }
}
```

The `SubscriptionWebSocketConfigurator` was refactored to accept a `ElideSettingsBuilderCustomizer` in order to customize the exception handler.


## How Has This Been Tested?
Added the appropriate unit and integration tests.

